<div class='elementListBrownSeparator'></div>
<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/702365-for-me-invitation-to-a-beheading-is-the">For me &quot;Invitation to a Beheading&quot; is the greatest piece of prose of all time. Nabokov detested a comparison to Orwell, he opined that the &quot;how&quot; matters and not the &quot;what&quot; (about). Indeed, its language (in Russian) is incredible. I reread many paragraphs as a pure joy of the language command. 
The main idea of the book should nevertheless be clear for all; it defines what Freedom is. Can you tell me what it is?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_702365'><a id="like_count_community_question_702365" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/702365?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">14 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F376561.Invitation_to_a_Beheading">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/702365-for-me-invitation-to-a-beheading-is-the">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/702365-for-me-invitation-to-a-beheading-is-the">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/15840956-rick-patterson"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1356672864i/15840956._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/15840956-rick-patterson">Rick Patterson</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Could Nabokov--a great skeptic about isms at the best of times--be advocating existentialism here? Cincinnatus is so similar to characters like Camus&apos;<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Could Nabokov--a great skeptic about isms at the best of times--be advocating existentialism here? Cincinnatus is so similar to characters like Camus' Meursault and the narrator of Sartre's "The Wall" that it's hard not to make the comparison. Then Freedom would indeed be a playful detachment from capital-M Meaning.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
